    <h4 style="margin-top: 40px;">
      LEADERSHIP & MARKETING POSITIONS<br>
    </h4>
      <p style="clear:left;">
      This is the most important role at ThinQ.tv. It is your opportunity to be on the ground floor of a movement to create the future of participatory thought-provoking entertainment.<br><br>
      Seeking engaging self-starters to coordinate live online thought-provoking conversations. Successful candidate(s) will gain leadership skills and user research experience while using technology to foster community engagement and encourage conversations about innovation, faith, or people-to-people ambassadorship.<br><br></p>

      <p style="font-weight: bold;">Learning Outcomes:</p>
      <p>
        - Leadership skills<br>
        - Teamwork with in-person and remote colleagues<br>
        - Researching user behavior to define effective methods for online community-building<br>
      </p><br>

      <p style="font-weight: bold;">Responsibilities:</p>
      <p>
      - Invite organizations and individuals to participate in live conversations<br>
      - Participate in live online conversations on Tuesday, Wednesday, or Thursday evenings<br>
      - Recruit users to participate in ThinQ.tv conversations on Tuesday, Wednesday, and Thursday evenings<br>
      - Set up speaking engagements for Dr. Schaefer<br>
      - Share announcements and content on social media
      </p><br>
      <p style="font-weight: bold;">Qualifications:</p>
      <p>
      - Demonstrated an ability to accomplish goals through previous academic, volunteer, or work experience<br>
      - Excellent conversational and writing skills
      </p>
  </div>

