        RUBY ON RAILS DEVELOPERS<br>
      </h4>
      <p style="clear:left;"> 
      Seeking interns and open source developers who are passionate about creating and participating on an online platform where people can drop in for fellowship and share their experiences. You will learn Ruby on Rails by working with the existing code base for ThinQ.tv. This is your opportunity to be a part of a developers bootcamp taught by a highly educated, experienced software engineer - free of charge. <br><br>

      The internship will only be offered to the most highly motivated and qualified candidates (working on MS in Computer Science or other significant experience in MVC architecture or object-oriented software engineering). If you do not have sufficient object-oriented experience, you are encouraged to apply for our UX/UI (front end Ruby on Rails) position. <br><br>
      </p>
      <p style="font-weight: bold;">Learning Outcomes:</p>
      <p>
        - Ruby on Rails<br>
        - Test Driven Development in MiniTest<br>
        - Real-world experience at a tech startup
      </p>  <br>

    <p style="font-weight: bold;">Responsibilities:</p>
    <p>
    - Participate in live online conversations at least twice per week<br>
    - You are required to begin installation of the environment on your machine in advance of meeting with us. Go to <a href="https://github.com/ece106/tomatocan" target="_blank"style="font-weight: bold;"> https://github.com/ece106/tomatocan </a> for instructions.<br>
    - Write tests to expand the current test suite for Test Driven Development<br>
    - Recruit colleagues to talk about their tech or international experiences on ThinQ.tv<br><br>
    </p>
    <p style="font-weight: bold;">Qualifications:</p>
    <p>- Minimum: Demonstrated an ability to accomplish goals through previous academic, volunteer, or work experience. Significant experience in an object-oriented language.<br>
    - Preferred: Familiarity with Ruby, JavaScript, HTML, CSS, SQL.<br><br>
    </p>
  </div>
